[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Premier League is 25 years old this week and has been the home of some of the greatest players of the modern era.
But who would make your all-time Premier League XI?
Well, now you can pick your favourites from the shortlist selected by a panel of BBC experts and then share your picks with your friends.
Gary Lineker, Alan Shearer, Ian Wright and Danny Murphy picked their goalkeeper and defence on the first Premier League Show of the new season - and you can watch this on the BBC iPlayer now.
You can find out who they selected in midfield and attack on the next Premier League Show, which starts at 22:00 BST on BBC Two on Thursday, 24 August - as well as the most popular team selected by BBC users.
